body_html:
Yeap it works, this way (using transformations strip_unused_nodes, remove_nodes, all those folds, then round_weights and eightbit) my graph does not crashes anymore when used in android, like it did when I have used python scripts.

However, final_result layer works the same in just stripped version as in eightbit, but the second one (final_result_musoth - originally referenced as final_result_b) produces completely wrong results when graph is converted to eightbit... There has to be some operation that somehow twists it. When just stripped, it works fine. Hope @andrewharp will find something. Thank you for your support guys, you are doing great job here.
